23/03/2008
TIRANA, Albania -- The number of victims of a series of blasts in a munitions depot near Tirana last Saturday reached 21 after another body was found late on Friday (March 21st). Around 1,000 soldiers and rescue team members continue to search for victims at the site of the blasts, which injured 3000 people and destroyed 412 houses. Meanwhile, Albanian media reported that former Defence Minister Fatmir Mediu, who resigned after the tragedy, has been questioned in relation to the blasts. Mediu was summoned by investigators as a "witness, who is familiar with the situation". (MIA, Focus - 22/03/08)
